The paper deals with the Minimum Dominating Set problem on intersection graphs of geometric objects, specifically rectangles and L-frames. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in approximation algorithms (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions the problem being NP-hard and APX-hard, which falls under complexity theory (cs.CC).
